(202, 1, '2013-02-05 10:17:39', '2013-02-04 23:17:39', '<div class="sub-page-content">\r\n<div class="sub-page-content-left">\r\n<div class="sub-page-info">\r\n<h2>MYOB Training</h2>\r\n<strong><span>Extensive experience in MYOB training</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright size-full wp-image-231" alt="myob-logos" src="http://leyven.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/myob-logos1.jpg" width="321" height="110" data-id="231" />Whether you have a current staff member that needs\r\nadditional training or a new staff member, Leyven\r\nBookkeeping has extensive experience in training small\r\nbusiness staff in the procedures required to accurately\r\nrecord business transactions using MYOB products for a\r\nPC or a MAC.\r\n\r\nWe are trained to use MYOB to its full capacity. This means that you save time and money when previously manual\r\nprocesses are automated.\r\n\r\nWe believe in getting it right from the start!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'MYOB Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '110-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-02-05 10:17:39', '2013-02-04 23:17:39', '', 110, 'http://leyven.com.au/110-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(203, 1, '2013-01-26 09:23:15', '2013-01-25 22:23:15', '<div class="content-wrapper">\r\n<div class="page-content">\r\n<div class="page-left">\r\n<div class="left-title">\r\n<h4>Bookkeeping service for Sydney Hills District businesses</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<div class="left-content">\r\n\r\nLeyven Bookkeeping Pty Ltd is a CPA Business located in the beautiful\r\nHills District of northwest Sydney and was established by its principal,\r\nEvelyn (Eve) Durham to provide bookkeeping excellence to small\r\nbusinesses.\r\n<div class="box">\r\n\r\nAll general bookkeeping tasks including reviewing your current bus-\r\niness bookkeeping methods, training &amp; workers compensation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="box">\r\n\r\nBAS (Business Activity Statement) advice, preparation &amp; lodgement\r\nand dealing with commissioner on your behalf.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="box">\r\n\r\nManagement of GST including transaction coding. We will make\r\nsure all GST reports are submitted accurately and on time.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="box">\r\n\r\nBookkeeping training and MYOB training to help improve the per-\r\nformance of both you and your staff.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="box">\r\n\r\nWe offer a small business consulting service to help you understand\r\nfinancial reports, develop systems and solve problems.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nCall us today on <strong>0414 899 487</strong> <a href="#"><img src="http://leyven.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/leave-message.png" alt="" title="leave-message" width="162" height="38" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-100 message" /></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="page-right">\r\n<div class="buttons">\r\n<div class="bottons">\r\n<h3>BAS</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bottons">\r\n<h3>GST</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bottons">\r\n<h3>MYOB</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bottons">\r\n<h3>PAYG</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right-content">\r\n<h2>Overview of the bookkeeping services we can provide.</h2>\r\nAre you looking for a bookkeeper with extensive small business accounting\r\nexperience?\r\n\r\n<strong>Small Business Owners</strong> - When it comes to making important business\r\ndecisions, access to accurate and up to date information about your business\r\nis crucial. Leyven Bookkeeping can help you make this happen.\r\n\r\n<strong>Professional Accountants</strong> - Experience counts. Leyven Bookkeeping knows\r\nwhat you expect from a bookkeeping service. We can provide your valued\r\nclients with general bookkeeping or a specialised reviewer bookkeeping\r\nservice. Call Eve on <strong>0414 899 487</strong> <a href="#">More...</a>\r\n<h2>About our main bookkeeper - Eve Durham.</h2>\r\nEve is a CPA with a Bachelor of Economics (major in Accounting). Prior to\r\ncreating her own business, Eve gained more than 20 years experience in a\r\nchartered firm environment, including 6 years with KPMG. Eve is required to\r\nupdate her professional knowledge regularly and to maintain a high level of\r\nquality control in her business. <a href="#">More...</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '96-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-01-26 09:23:15', '2013-01-25 22:23:15', '', 96, 'http://leyven.com.au/96-revision-10/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(161, 1, '2013-01-28 13:45:00', '2013-01-28 02:45:00', '				<div class="sub-page-content">\r\n					<div class="sub-page-content-left">\r\n						<div class="sub-page-info">\r\n							<h2>Accounting</h2>\r\n							<p><span><strong>Here are some of the issues facing business today. Is this you?</strong></span></p>\r\n							<p>Are you already in business? </p>\r\n							<p>Thinking about going into business?</p>\r\n							<p>Do have an established business?</p>\r\n							<p>Do you not have enough time in business?</p>\r\n							<p>Do you need some specific support in your business?</p>\r\n							<p>Too many things to worry about and just want to get on with business?</p>\r\n							<p>Need someone to provide an independent unbiased view on business matters?</p>\r\n							<p>Your accountant may or may not do all this work, or they may do, it depends on their size and their status, for example, registered tax agents lodging business tax returns would not provide solutions for a lot of the above.  With respect to accountants, you generally visit their office and they do get “snowed under” with accounting work that stifles their efforts to go out and visit their customers and talk about their business.  Usually you contact your account when you have a specific problem, want specific advice, or when its tax time at end of year.  What about all the in between times, who do you talk to then?</p>\r\n							<p><span><strong>What’s your reason to be in business, let’s consider the following, as we all have different reasons (believe it or not), do you want to:</strong></span></p>\r\n							<ol>\r\n							<li>Be your own boss</li>\r\n							<li>Build sales and your territory</li>\r\n							<li>Build an empire</li>\r\n							<li>Buy a job</li>\r\n							<li>lways own some type of business i.e. newsagency</li>\r\n							<li>Move to an area that you want to live in and buy a business</li>\r\n							<li>Buy a franchise, where a lot of the worry has already been taken out of your hands, feel secure that established procedures, training and support is in place</li>\r\n							<li>Just be in business at some stage of your life</li></ol>\r\n							<p>Whatever the reason, some people choose the wrong reason or are just not suited, yes, they are their own worst enemy. Others go into business and fulfill their desire to do so, then leave the business and go back to paid \r\n							employment (I did… but know I am back in my own business).</p>\r\n							<p>Whatever the reason, it still poses those issues above, or others they may not be there.  There is a solution, and I put my skills and experience to you to contribute to your outcomes.</p>\r\n							<p>Can I let you know that I have talked to many people in small business, I have a passion for assessing performances of business, especially where I go and buy something.  I can very quickly judge if that business managed well and what the business owner(s) expect.  I can critical if customer service is below par, relative to what I am paying and what is expected, and I compliment owners and employees when service impresses me.  That’s my passion, and I offer that to you.  Take a few seconds more to read my simple but effective way of the growth cycle of a managing a business.</p><ol>\r\n							<li>INFANCY STAGE     -   Start Up  -  from scratch or taking over an existing business</li>\r\n							<li>ADOLESCENT STAGE  -  Start of stability, growth and repeat business – it’s growing…….</li>\r\n							<li>MATURITY AND BEYOND  -  further expansion, my business is leaving “home”….</li></ol>\r\n							<p>These three (3) cycles of evolution present many different challenges to you, to family, and to the business itself (which is paramount).  The business is not a person, but treat it as such, with respect and it should return the favour. I can help you with these matters, my relationship with you is important. </p>\r\n						</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n		', 'Consulting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '108-revision-13', '', '', '2013-01-28 13:45:00', '2013-01-28 02:45:00', '', 108, 'http://leyven.com.au/108-revision-13/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
